{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3360958,"name":"","username":"griffingreat1","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/71e660/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-04-13T13:40:12.850Z","cooked":"<p>So I ran into a problem during our first event where our robot would reverse its heading when we were on red alliance but was fine on blue alliance.<br>
Our auto was made with pathplanner with the mirroring option.<br>
The auto would work fine, but when teleop started, our driver quickly found out that the controls were reversed, as if the robot had reoriented itself to the blue alliance side (“forward” on the joystick was now towards the red driver station). As a temporary fix for comp I just made the robot reverse the controls when on red but removed it after comp because I wanted to actually fix the problem. With advantageScope I was able to see that when the robot was on red, at the start of auto the swerve rotation value changed itself from 0 to 180, which to me looks like that was the problem. Currently I have it so that in the teleopinit() function, if the DriverStation says it is on red alliance it just calls a command to reset the robots pose to the robots current x and y and the robots current rotation - 180 degrees.</p>
<p>This fixed the problem and our robot was working fine with this for comp, but I don’t think I did it right and I want to check that there isn’t a better way to do this that I didn’t know about, since this is my first year using pathplanner and the field mirroring for auto.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2024-04-13T13:40:12.850Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":102,"reads":157,"readers_count":156,"score":541.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":462576,"topic_slug":"gyro-heading-reverses-itself-after-running-auto","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":59845,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"2815 lead programmer"},"post_url":"/t/gyro-heading-reverses-itself-after-running-auto/462576/1","custom_user_title":"2815 lead programmer","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3360981,"name":"Dan Langdon","username":"woodworker2001","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/w/bbe5ce/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-04-13T14:32:27.935Z","cooked":"<p>You actually hit the recommended fix… PathPlanner always drives as if you are the blue alliance.  So you need to invert your x and y joystick controls when you are on the red alliance.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2024-04-13T14:32:27.935Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":7,"reads":135,"readers_count":134,"score":82.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":462576,"topic_slug":"gyro-heading-reverses-itself-after-running-auto","display_username":"Dan Langdon","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":51496,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/gyro-heading-reverses-itself-after-running-auto/462576/2","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3361150,"name":"Carlos Salazar","username":"StarbuckBarista","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/starbuckbarista/{size}/186251_2.png","created_at":"2024-04-13T18:20:58.211Z","cooked":"<p>Here are some snippet from our team’s code which should sovle the issue!</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">IntSupplier allianceOriented = () -&gt; {

    if (!DriverStation.getAlliance().isPresent()) { return -1; }
    return DriverStation.getAlliance().get() == Alliance.Red ? 1 : -1;
};

this.swerve.setDefaultCommand(new Drive(
    this.swerve, 
    () -&gt; MathUtil.applyDeadband(this.driverOne.getHID().getLeftY() * allianceOriented.getAsInt(), Constants.SwerveConstants.TRANSLATION_DEADBAND),
    () -&gt; MathUtil.applyDeadband(this.driverOne.getHID().getLeftX() * allianceOriented.getAsInt(), Constants.SwerveConstants.TRANSLATION_DEADBAND),
    () -&gt; MathUtil.applyDeadband(this.driverOne.getHID().getRightX(), Constants.SwerveConstants.OMEGA_DEADBAND)
));
</code></pre>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">public void zeroGyro () {

    Translation2d translation = this.getPose().getTranslation();
    Rotation2d rotation = new Rotation2d();

    if (DriverStation.getAlliance().isPresent() &amp;&amp; DriverStation.getAlliance().get() == Alliance.Red) {

        Rotation2d allianceOriented = Rotation2d.fromDegrees(180);
        rotation = rotation.plus(allianceOriented); 
    }

    this.resetOdometry(new Pose2d(translation, rotation));
}
</code></pre>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2024-04-13T18:26:20.493Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":6,"reads":112,"readers_count":111,"score":72.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":462576,"topic_slug":"gyro-heading-reverses-itself-after-running-auto","display_username":"Carlos Salazar","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":51496,"username":"woodworker2001","name":"Dan Langdon","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/w/bbe5ce/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":57451,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Programming & Electrical Captain"},"post_url":"/t/gyro-heading-reverses-itself-after-running-auto/462576/3","custom_user_title":"Programming & Electrical Captain","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3361569,"name":"","username":"griffingreat1","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/71e660/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-04-14T02:50:55.281Z","cooked":"<p>but is my solution of just resetting pose to be 180 degrees less also fine? like will it still work fine or would it be best to change it to this?</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2024-04-14T02:50:55.281Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"read